I mean the dad is definitely not the evil for the sake of evil type. The great thing about this book is not that we see some disney villain go up on a tantrum and beat up his daughter for no reason. He lost his mind and his trust in the world when his wife (who was either a traitorous bitch whore who belongs on the streets or just someone who could not deal with his violent tendencies, but still is an asshole either way for leaving her daughter with this madman) took off, and was right, albeit tilting the scales in his side by using a cowardly but nonetheless little boy as evidence that there is no goodness in the world. He's a bad guy, but you feel for him too. The story's depressing because it seems so real: this is what a traumatized man is very probably going to do and this is how a child very probably would react upon seeing such a scene.

1735. I read something about the artist being scarred herself (yes it's a woman), and releasing these doujins as some kind of therapy. 

This being uploaded in the context of the website nhentai, where the sole purpose is to nut, might make her releases somewhat.... infamous. To me, these stories touch upon some rather serious topics (taken to the very extreme), with the cover being that of a typical nhentai upload, NOT the other way around. And depending on which angle one approaches it from, his or her emotions will vastly differ. Not saying people should change their opinion of these works being disgusting... but if you're one of those people that happened to read to the end of my comment, like I said, try approaching it from a different angle, perhaps that might serve as soft therapy for the traumatizing material you've been exposed to.
